Comfycreations here, with an eight chapter of Roo'd for you guys, alongside the prose rewrite for the story I've been looking forward to doing for a long time. I probably sound like a broken record with how much I say it, but I'm sorry it took me this long to get both of these done, and I hope the length and amount of the new content to read makes up for it. For those curious if they should read the prose rewrite if they've already read the first five chapters before, I'd say there's a lot of additions there that add to the story and characters even if the plot didn't change much.

I really appreciate the patience and support from all those who've read the story and have continued to look forward to it despite my delays, it really means the world to me.

The 49.3k word update for A Roo'd Awakening alongside the 70k~ word rewrite can now be found on Ao3 here: https://archiveofourown.org/works/42365598

And if you prefer to read on Rentry: https://rentry.org/RoodChapterEight

Album with all story related art can be found here: https://catbox.moe/c/agt3hn

Though please note I've only added a couple of new things there that are related to the update. I'll be adding all the missing images soon, since I didn't really want to wait any longer to post this. As always, I appreciate any and all feedback/criticism no matter what it is as it really helps me make any future stuff even better for you guys. I hope you enjoy this update as much as I've enjoyed writing it for you.

Lastly I'd like to thank a few very important people for helping me make the update and rewrite possible. I'd like to give Tious a huge thanks for his help throughout the entire process with his feedback, ideas, proofreading and even more that I struggle to put into words properly. I'd also like to give credit where it's due to Scuds, Zzx, Hoc, DV, Mek and Idontwantthis for their contributions to either the rewrite or the update with their comprehensive feedback and suggestions.

He notes how some sources claim them to be savages and man eaters, while others say that they live in communities with trades and interact with other people as well as their own customs and morals. some say through languages, and some say they had none but barking. Ratramnus then uses aristotilian logic (predicates and subjects, epistomology, theology etc) to determine that the operative nature that makes a human a human, that is a godly creature, is higher rationality and sapience, not necissarily a particular flesh, so if the supposed creature of the cynocephali demonstrated features indicative of a "human soul" it is essentially and fundementally human and should thus be a subject to be preached to rather than treated as a beast.
